<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="FO4" checkit-title="Exact First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
        Explain why one of the following ODEs is exact, and why the other is not.
    </p>
      <me>-10 \, t y - 10 \, y {y'} = 5 \, t^{2} {y'} + 15 \, t^{2}</me><me>-6 \, t^{2} y {y'} - 10 \, t y {y'} + 10 \, t y = -4 \, y</me>
    <p>
      Then find an implicit solution for the exact ODE
      that satisfies the initial value
        <m>y(1)=-1</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>The following ODE is exact.</p>
      <me>-10 \, t y - 10 \, y {y'} = 5 \, t^{2} {y'} + 15 \, t^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Its implicit solution satisfying the initial value is:
    </p>
      <me>5 \, t^{3} + 5 \, t^{2} y + 5 \, y^{2} = 5</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
